newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-LAST QUOTES - Australian Eurobond benchmarks.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-LAST QUOTES - Australian Eurobond benchmarks.

text.p: Last quotes from the International Securities Market Association for benchmark Australian dollar Eurobonds issued by Australian entities.
The Western Australia Treasury Corporation issued a A$200 million three year eurobond through lead manager Nomura International overnight.
The bonds, which mature on January 21, 2000, pay a 6.00 percent semi-annual coupon and carry a 100.138 issue price. Payment date is January 21, 1997.
JP Morgan Australia also tapped the eurobond market overnight, issuing a A$100 million three year bond through lead manager Toronto Dominion.
The bonds mature on February 24, 2000, pay a 6.75 percent annual coupon. Issue price is 101.395 and payment date is February 24, 1997.
